        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "AnyCable is an open-source WebSocket server written in Go with built-in delivery guarantees, presence tracking, and message ordering. It works with any backend — Ruby on Rails, Laravel, Node.js/TypeScript, Python/FastAPI, or any language that can make HTTP requests — via its pub/sub HTTP API. AnyCable handles 10,000+ concurrent connections per server and has been in production since 2017, powering 50+ companies including Doximity, CoinGecko, Jobber, and Circle."
