        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How is AnyCable different from Socket.io?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Socket.io is a JavaScript library that provides WebSocket transport — you build reliability, presence, and authentication yourself. AnyCable is a standalone server with delivery guarantees, presence tracking, message ordering, and authentication built in. AnyCable works with any backend (not just Node.js), and because it's a separate process, WebSocket connections survive application deploys."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
